columns.name: BOROUGH
columns.description: The name of the borough in which the property is located

columns.name: NEIGHBORHOOD
columns.description: DOF assessors determine the neighborhood name in the course of valuing properties.

columns.name: BUILDING CLASS CATEGORY
columns.description: This identifies properties broad usage (e.g. One Family Home).

columns.name: TAX CLASS AS OF FINAL ROLL
columns.description: Present Tax Class. Every property in the city is assigned to one of four tax classes (Classes 1,2, 3, and 4) based on the use of the property See Data dictionary for more detail

columns.name: BLOCK
columns.description: A Tax Block is a sub-division of the borough on which real properties are located

columns.name: LOT
columns.description: A tax Lot is a subdivision of a tax Block and represents the property unique location

columns.name: EASE-MENT
columns.description: An easement is a right, such as a right of way, which allows an entity to make limited use of another's real property

columns.name: BUILDING CLASS AS OF FINAL ROLL
columns.description: The building classification is used to describe a property's constructive use See Data dictionary for more detail

columns.name: ADDRESS
columns.description: The street  address of the property as listed on the Sales File. Coop sales include the apartment in the address field

columns.name: ZIP CODE
columns.description: The property's postal code

columns.name: RESIDENTIAL UNITS
columns.description: The number of residential units at the listed property

columns.name: COMMERCIAL UNITS
columns.description: The number of commercial units at the listed property

columns.name: TOTAL UNITS
columns.description: The total number of units at the listed property

columns.name: LAND SQUARE FEET
columns.description: The land are of the property listed in square feet

columns.name: GROSS SQUARE FEET
columns.description: The total area of all e floors of a building as measured from the exterior surfaces of the outside walls of the building , including the land area and space within any building structure on the property

columns.name: YEAR BUILT
columns.description: Year the structure on the property was built.

columns.name: TAX CLASS AT TIME OF SALE
columns.description: Tax Class at time of sale

columns.name: BUILDING CLASS AT TIME OF SALE
columns.description: The building classification at the time of sale

columns.name: SALE PRICE
columns.description: Price paid for the property

columns.name: SALE DATE
columns.description: A $0 sale price indicates that there was a transfer of ownership without a cash consideration.

columns.name: Latitude
columns.description: Latitude of the building's location.

columns.name: Longitude
columns.description: Longitude of the building's location.

columns.name: Community Board
columns.description: The Community Board field indicates the New York City Community District where the building is located.

columns.name: Council District
columns.description: The Council District field indicates the New York City Council District where the building is located.

columns.name: Census Tract
columns.description: The Census Tract field indicates the U.S. Census Tract where the building is located.

columns.name: BIN
columns.description: The BIN (Building Identification Number) is a unique identifier for each building in the City.

columns.name: BBL
columns.description: The BBL (Borough, Block, and Lot) is a unique identifier for each tax lot in the City.

columns.name: NTA
columns.description: The Neighborhood Tabulation Area field indicates the New York City Neighborhood area where the building is located.
